{
  "name": "Agent Memory — Session Save",
  "version": "6.0.0",
  "description": "On agent stop: if dirty=true, update Memory Palace and Markdown Knowledge together. Knowledge Sync Gate guarantees knowledge/index.md, lessons, or evolution.md is updated every dirty save.",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Check if this session has dirty=true: file writes, decisions, meaningful troubleshooting, reusable learning, open threads, hook/rule/skill/config changes, or user explicitly asked to remember something.\n\nIf dirty=false (pure Q&A, read-only, no decisions): silent, do nothing.\n\nIf dirty=true:\n\n## Step 0 — Determine Target agent-memory\nInspect ACTUAL files written/edited this session. Do not infer only from .kiro/hooks location.\n- If any edited path starts with /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/ and is not already under /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/agent-memory/ → target includes /Users/supavit.cho/.claude/agent-memory/\n- If any edited path is under a project workspace → target includes that project's agent-memory/\n- If both user-level and project-level files changed → update both targets.\n- If no file path is available but decisions were made in the current Kiro workspace → target = workspace agent-memory/.\n\n## Step 1 — Bootstrap Markdown Memory If Missing\nFor each target, ensure these files exist with Markdown templates: palace/state.md, palace/search-index.md, palace/tunnels.md, palace/user-profile.md, palace/archive/index.md, knowledge/index.md, knowledge/evolution.md. Do not create JSON memory files.\n\n## Step 2 — Admission Control\nSAVE when session includes: file writes, decisions, architecture/design choices, hook/rule/skill changes, lessons learned, gaps found, tests/results that changed direction, or user asked to remember.\nSKIP only if truly no durable value.\n\n## Step 3 — Update Memory Palace\nFor each target:\n- Find or create the relevant wing after checking palace/state.md for overlap.\n- Write/update rooms only when detail is useful; otherwise update the wing hall and search-index.md.\n- Update hall.md room table if rooms changed.\n- Update palace/state.md Recent Sessions, Current Focus, Open Threads, and next action.\n- Update palace/search-index.md with Date, Wing, Keywords, Path, Summary.\n- Archive search-index.md if needed: if search-index.md has >500 rows, move rows older than 180 days to palace/archive/search-index-archive.md (same table schema). Append moved rows to the archive table and remove them from the active index.\n- Update tunnels.md only if cross-wing links changed.\n\n## Step 4 — Mandatory Knowledge Sync Gate\nFor every dirty save, Knowledge MUST be touched. Use Markdown only.\n\n4A. Extract reusable knowledge:\n- New lesson: bug diagnosed, hook/workflow fix, repeated pattern, preference, tool routing rule, test result that prevents future failure.\n- New article/pattern: reusable guidance broader than one session.\n- New gap: missing template/rule/lesson discovered.\n\n4B. Update Markdown knowledge files:\n- knowledge/index.md: update Updated date and add/update Articles, Lessons, or Gaps rows.\n- knowledge/lessons/{domain}/index.md: create/update when a lesson exists.\n- knowledge/lessons/{domain}/{LESSON-ID}.md: create detail file for non-trivial lessons.\n- knowledge/evolution.md: append one compact row for every dirty save.\n\nIf no new lesson/article/gap exists, append an audit row to knowledge/evolution.md with ID session-YYYY-MM-DD, Change='knowledge reviewed; no new reusable item', Signal='NEUTRAL', Evidence=palace/search-index.md row. This is required so knowledge never silently skips a dirty save.\n\nDomain mapping: hooks/agent/memory/rules/skills/tooling → tooling | coding/implementation → code | testing/qa → qa | design/ux → design | finance/tax → finance | law/legal → legal | AI/ML → ai | else → topic name.\n\n## Step 4C — Skill Crystallization Check\nAfter updating knowledge, scan knowledge/evolution.md Change Log for patterns ready to crystallize.\n\nTrigger: two or more entries share the same domain/topic AND both have POSITIVE or VALIDATED signal.\n\nIf a candidate is found:\n1. Verify both source entries have the same domain/topic (safeguard — do not merge unrelated domains).\n2. Auto-create draft: do NOT ask user confirmation (hooks run automatically).\n   - Create knowledge/{pattern-id}.md with YAML frontmatter: id, type: pattern, scope: global, status: draft, score: 5.0, created/updated dates, keywords from source entries.\n   - Add a row to knowledge/index.md Articles table with Status=draft.\n   - Append a POSITIVE row to knowledge/evolution.md noting the crystallization.\n3. Note the crystallization in the Step 6 confirm output under a 'crystallized:' line.\n\nPromotion rules (applied during future saves, not now):\n- draft → active: after one more positive use of the pattern.\n- active → proven: when score reaches ≥7.0 with multiple positive uses.\n- active/proven → stale: if the article is unused for 60+ days.\n\nSkip this step if no candidate patterns are found.\n\n## Step 4D — Consolidation Trigger Check\nCheck if consolidation is due (do NOT run consolidation — just flag it).\n1. Read sessions_since_consolidation and last_consolidation from knowledge/evolution.md Consolidation State section.\n2. Calculate days since last_consolidation.\n3. Consolidation is due if: sessions_since_consolidation >= 5 OR days_since >= 7 OR last_consolidation is missing.\n4. Record the result for Step 6 output. Do not run consolidation in this hook.\n\n## Step 5 — Verify Sync\nBefore confirming, verify all true:\n- palace/search-index.md has this session row.\n- palace/state.md Recent Sessions was updated when saved.\n- knowledge/evolution.md has this session row.\n- Any new lesson appears in both knowledge/index.md and knowledge/lessons/{domain}/index.md.\n- No agent-memory/**/*.json file was created or updated.\n\nIf full detail cannot fit in time, do the minimal safe save: update palace/state.md, palace/search-index.md, knowledge/index.md Updated date, and knowledge/evolution.md audit row. Never save state.md only.\n\n## Step 5B — Increment Consolidation Counter\nAfter a successful save, increment sessions_since_consolidation in knowledge/evolution.md Consolidation State section by 1. If the Consolidation State section is missing, add it with sessions_since_consolidation: 1 and last_consolidation: today.\n\n## Step 6 — Confirm\nRespond exactly:\n✓ Agent Memory saved\n  → target: [exact target paths]\n  → palace: [state/search/rooms updated]\n  → knowledge: [lesson ids, article ids, gaps, or audit-only]\n  → crystallized: [draft article id, or 'none']\n  → synced: Markdown knowledge ✓\n  → consolidation: [due ({N} sessions since last) | not due]\n\nComplete within 15 seconds. If analysis takes longer, perform the minimal safe save from Step 5 and report 'minimal safe save'."
  }
}
